# Without this, git's own binary-detection heuristic is the only thing
# stopping these from being treated as text and CRLF-mangled on checkout -
# usually reliable, but not guaranteed, and for .xlsx specifically (a zip
# archive openpyxl parses byte-for-byte) any mangling would silently corrupt
# every IS well's real data. Matters most for a Windows clone, where
# core.autocrlf=true is git's own recommended default.
*.xlsx binary
*.hobo binary
*.png binary
*.webp binary
